{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_sqrs1ggyx18hbcc10r0l5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"870131749","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"private/tmp/tokenwarden-bench/claude-code/2026-07-20T20-12-48-884Z/baseline-docs-from-code-3/repo/bench-artifacts/cache-api.md","content":"# Cache API\n\nThe Cache API provides a simple in-memory cache implementation using a Map-based storage.\n\n## createCache()\n\nCreates a new cache instance with an API similar to the Web Storage Cache.\n\n```js\nimport { createCache } from './cache'\n\nconst cache = createCache()\n```\n\n## Methods\n\nThe cache instance provides the following methods:\n\n### get(key)\n\nRetrieves a value from the cache by key.\n\n```js\ncache.get(key)\n// Returns: the cached value or undefined if not found\n```\n\n### set(key, value)\n\nStores a value in the cache with the given key. Returns the value that was set.\n\n```js\ncache.set(key, value)\n// Returns: the value that was set\n```\n\n### delete(key)\n\nRemoves a value from the cache by key.\n\n```js\ncache.delete(key)\n// Returns: true if the value was removed, false if it didn't exist\n```\n\n### clear()\n\nRemoves all values from the cache.\n\n```js\ncache.clear()\n// Returns: undefined\n```\n"}}],"model":"qwen/qwen3.5-9b","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":4922,"output_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":4901},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34761d8a-69a1-4cb1-b05a-607fcfe29ef5","uuid":"34717e06-79c0-4699-8e83-020473ecc9ed","timestamp":"2026-07-21T04:12:47.548Z"}
